        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 6. Pagurus fungiformis, new species. Holotype male from Bitung, Sulawesi (sl 3.6 mm; MZB Cru 1506). A, shield and cephalic appendages, dorsal (setae omitted on left); B, ocular acicles and interocular lobe, dorsal; C, maxillule, ventral (coxal endite broken off); inset, endopod, lateral; D, left maxilla, ventral (setae omitted); E, left second maxilliped, ventral; F, left third maxilliped, lateral; G, ischium of left third maxilliped, dorsal; H, coxae of first to third pereopod and fifth and sixth thoracic sternites, ventral; I, anterior lobe of sixth thoracic sternite, ventral; J, coxae of fifth pereopods and eighth thoracic sternite, ventral; K, telson, dorsal." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4618864/files/figure.png" .

